    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Excitement Spreads</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Eric Lipton</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Estimated 3,000 New York City buses will soon be plastered with signs urging fans to pick a team in World Series (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Buses, subway cars and even some of the landmark buildings in Manhattan soon will be caught up in the Subway Series frenzy. The efforts come, not surprisingly, courtesy of Major League Baseball, which yesterday unveiled at City Hall what it is calling its ''Pledge Your Allegiance'' campaign.</p>
        <p>An estimated 3,000 buses will soon be plastered with signs urging fans to pick a team. The Empire State Building is to be lit up in team-inspired colors.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Buses, subway cars and even some of the landmark buildings in Manhattan soon will be caught up in the Subway Series frenzy. The efforts come, not surprisingly, courtesy of Major League Baseball, which yesterday unveiled at City Hall what it is calling its ''Pledge Your Allegiance'' campaign.</p>
        <p>An estimated 3,000 buses will soon be plastered with signs urging fans to pick a team. The Empire State Building is to be lit up in team-inspired colors.</p>
        <p>The league is working on plans to cover the pavement at 46th Street and Park Avenue and the main concourse floor of Grand Central Terminal with the ''Pledge Your Allegiance'' logos. And four subway cars -- two on the 4 line and two on the 7 line -- are to be enveloped in Yankee- or Met-themed wraps.</p>
        <p>Eric Lipton</p>
        <p>BASEBALL: SUBWAY SERIES -- YANKEES NOTEBOOK</p>
      </block>
